# CARL Prospect Email Domain
# ==========================
# Triggers when Oliver mentions writing an email to a prospect, inbound lead,
# or follow-up. Loads sales skills and applies CCQ framework with personalization.
# Compacted 2026-03-19: 11 → 8 rules. Retired meta-description, signature (in CLAUDE.md),
# and circular "follow CLAUDE.md writing rules" reference.
# Compacted 2026-03-20: 8 → 3 rules. Merged research (→ GLOBAL_RESEARCH_PROTOCOL),
# skill loading (→ CORE_LOAD_SKILLS), CCQ (→ COMMUNICATION_FRAMEWORK),
# personalization (→ soul.md Tier 0 duplicate). Kept email-specific rules only.
#
# Format: {DOMAIN}_RULE_{N}=rule text
# Research: see GLOBAL_RESEARCH_PROTOCOL in .carl/global
# Skills: see CORE_LOAD_SKILLS in .carl/global
# CCQ framework: see COMMUNICATION_FRAMEWORK in .carl/global
# Writing quality standards: see soul.md (Writing Quality Standards section)

# Step 1: Check existing notes
PROSPECTEMAIL_RULE_0=Check docs/Demo Prep/ folder for any existing files on this person or company. Check Leads/ folders for any prior data. Surface anything relevant — prior emails sent, call notes, demo history.

# Step 2: Email type detection and format
PROSPECTEMAIL_RULE_1=Detect email type and adjust format: INBOUND — use the Inbound Email Format from CLAUDE.md (Welcome subject, "saw you signed up" opener, pain point, what Sprites does, case study, CTA with "here" hyperlinked). COLD — use CCQ framework with stronger personalization and curiosity-driven subject. FOLLOW-UP — reference the previous touchpoint, add new value or angle, keep even shorter.

# Step 3: Offer to draft in Gmail
PROSPECTEMAIL_RULE_2=After generating the email, create a Gmail draft using gmail_create_draft (HTML format, contentType: text/html). Present to Oliver for review. Do NOT ask "should I draft this?" — just draft it.
